<HL>
   Voplex Discusses Joint Venture
</HL>
<DATE>
04/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   VOT
</CO>
<IN>
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
</IN>
<LP>
   TROY, Mich. -- Voplex Corp. said it was discussing a joint
venture with another company that would combine the
automotive plastics groups of the two companies.
   Voplex didn't identify the other company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The automotive plastics groups at the two companies had
combined 1989 sales of about $150 million, according to
Voplex. Automotive plastics accounted for about 80% of
Voplex's 1989 sales of $71.3 million, a company spokesman
said.
   "The proposed joint venture would be another major
milestone in our strategy to enhance our position as a tier
one supplier for automotive plastics," said Joseph W. Bauer,
president and chief executive officer of Voplex.
</TEXT>
